  <h1>To use the Public GeyserConnect for your Playstation,</h1>
  <p>
    you must use a LAN proxy software that relays the GeyserConnect server as a local connection,
    connecting to your choice of <code>us.geyserconnect.net</code> or <code>eu.geyserconnect.net</code> or
    <code>beta.geyserconnect.net</code> with port <code>19132</code>.
  </p>
  <h2>Android Device:</h2>
  <p>
    You can use either <a
      href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=pl.extollite.bedrocktogetherapp">BedrockTogether</a> or <a
      href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.smokiem.mcserverconnector">MC Server Connector</a> app.
  </p>
  <p>The <a href="https://ci.opencollab.dev/job/GeyserMC/job/GeyserAndroid/job/master/">GeyserMC Android app</a> is no
    longer maintained for new game versions, and is no longer a usable option.</p>
  <h2>iOS Device:</h2>
  <p>
    You can use either <a href="https://apps.apple.com/us/app/bedrocktogether/id1534593376">BedrockTogether</a> or <a
      href="https://apps.apple.com/us/app/mc-server-connector/id1548251304">MC Server Connector</a> app.
  </p>
  <h2>Computers:</h2>
  <p>
    Download and setup <a href="https://github.com/jhead/phantom">Phantom</a> on your computer.
  </p>
  <p>
    You may also run an Android emulator such as <a href="https://www.bluestacks.com/">Bluestacks</a> to run the apps
    mentioned above.
  </p>
</div>